        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 17 at 3:28AM CDT until August 17 at 4:15AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>SVRLOT

The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Will County in northeastern Illinois...
Eastern Kankakee County in northeastern Illinois...
Northern Newton County in northwestern Indiana...
Southern Lake County in northwestern Indiana...
Northern Jasper County in northwestern Indiana...

* Until 415 AM CDT.

* At 327 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Grant Park to 6 miles southeast of Beecher to
Lake Dalecarlia, moving southeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Thayer, Sumava Resorts, Roselawn, Mount Ayr, Stoutsburg, Momence,
DeMotte, Fair Oaks, Hopkins Park, Parr, Lowell, Schneider, Shelby,
Grant Park, Lake Village, Lake Dalecarlia, and Rensselaer.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
